# The `theme` file is the single source of truth for the current colorscheme
# (catppuccin-xxx). It is updated at runtime by the `theme` shell function
# (and read by nvim, ghostty, tmux, bat, etc.).
#
# We don't want runtime theme switches to dirty the working tree or risk
# accidental commits, so always treat changes to this file as if
# `git update-index --skip-worktree` had been run.
theme skip-worktree
